Story zones.

A story zone shows the player a passage of story text — a readable, multi-page message — when they enter it or interact with it. It's the entity for cutscene-style narration, lore the player can stop and read, a placard of exposition tied to a spot on the map, or a quiet beat where the game speaks a few lines before letting the player move on. The text is presented as a dialog the player reads through at their own pace, and the rest of the game pauses while they do.

How a story zone works.

The zone covers a rectangular area. When it triggers, the game pauses and the zone's text is shown as a dialog; if the text holds more than one line or page, the player advances through them one at a time, then closes the dialog and play resumes. Two settings shape when and how often it fires:

Trigger mode decides what sets it off — walking into the area, pressing the interact key while inside, or either.
Retriggerable decides whether it can fire again. When on, the zone fires every time its trigger condition is met; when off, it fires once and then stays quiet for the rest of the visit.

Story zone fields.

The story zone form takes the following:

Coordinates. A minimum and maximum x and y (and a minimum and maximum z on 3d maps), marking the area that holds the story.

Text. The passage to show. Separate each line or page with two dashes, and the dialog presents them in turn.

Story sound (a folder name from the story sounds list, or none). The audio theme for the dialog; the bundle supplies an open cue, a scroll cue heard as the player moves through the text, and a close cue. Pick none for a silent dialog.

Mode. When the zone fires — step (the moment the player walks in), press (while the player is inside and presses the interact key), or step or press (either one).

Retriggerable (checkbox). When checked, the zone fires every time it's triggered; when unchecked, it fires only the first time and then never again. Checked by default.

Auditioning sounds in the builder.

While the story sound list is focused in the form, press space to hear the scroll clip of the highlighted theme, hold control and press L to hear its open clip, and hold control and press H to hear its close clip.

Authoring story zones by hand.

If you edit main.sif directly, a story zone is: story_zone minx maxx miny maxy "text" storytype mode retriggerable. On 3d maps a minimum and maximum z follow the y pair: story_zone minx maxx miny maxy minz maxz "text" storytype mode retriggerable. The text is wrapped in double quotes so it may contain spaces, with two dashes marking each line break. Mode is the word step, press, or both. Retriggerable is the literal word true or false, and the story sound must match a story sounds folder name or the word none.
